1.body: EasyMl-Plugins is an API that allows adding functionalities within EasyML. At the moment, plugins of the following types can be added: Provider : will aim to return data within a certain period of time. Hook : send the details regarding a found anomaly to an external system
1.title: What is EasyML Plugins

10.body:
1. Define your first Plugin class. public class HelloWorldPlugin extends ProviderPlugin { public HelloWorldPlugin() { super("Hello World", "1.0.0"); } @Override public void onEnable() { getLogger().info("Plugin Hello World enabled"); } @Override public void onCreate(@NotNull UUID id) { } @Override public @NotNull List<Serie> getSeries(@NotNull UUID id) { return List.of( new Serie("temp", "temperature") ); } @Override public @NotNull LinkedList<TimedValue> getSerieData(@NotNull UUID id, @NotNull String serieId, @NotNull Instant start, @NotNull Instant end) { var now = Instant.now(); var list = new LinkedList<TimedValue>(); list.add(new TimedValue(now, 25.0)); list.add(new TimedValue(now.plusSeconds(60), 26.0)); list.add(new TimedValue(now.plusSeconds(120), 27.0)); list.add(new TimedValue(now.plusSeconds(180), 28.0)); return list; } @Override public boolean status(@NotNull UUID id) { return true; }
} 2. Now you can do the build and the .jar file you can place it in /easyml/plugins/providers. 3. Congratulations! You have created your first plugin.
10.title: Start programming

2.body: Learn how to install and integrate EasyML Plugins in your projects.
2.title: Installation

5.body:
1. Add the JitPack repository to your build file. <repositories> <repository> <id>jitpack.io</id> <url>https://jitpack.io</url> </repository>
</repositories> 2. Add the dependency. <dependency> <groupId>com.github.qlsolutions.easyml-plugins</groupId> <artifactId>api</artifactId> <version>0.10.1</version> <scope>provided</scope>
</dependency> 3. Once you’re done, you may now proceed creating your first plugin .
5.title: Installation

8.body:
1. Add the JitPack repository to your build file. dependencyResolutionManagement { repositoriesMode.set(RepositoriesMode.FAIL_ON_PROJECT_REPOS) repositories { mavenCentral() maven { url 'https://jitpack.io' } }
} 2. Add the dependency. compileOnly("com.github.qlsolutions.easyml-plugins:api:0.10.1") 3. Once you’re done, you may now proceed creating your first plugin .
